      • run

        public java.util.Date run()
        Description copied from interface: HeartbeatListener
        Find and run all Events that are Queued and past their schedule time. It is always legal for this method to return null but if a Date is returned it is an indication of the next queued event handled by the class and may be used to optimise the heart-beat frequency.

        run in interface HeartbeatListener
